=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Classes_Trig1_ex1 ===

DESCRIPTION: A very_dark pure_tone sound, with complex oscillator character around 800 Hz, featuring very_slow attack and percussive envelope, with chaotic spectral movement, filtered with steep_rolloff character, and spectrally simple.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: very_slow
  brightness: very_dark
  crest_factor_db: percussive
  envelope_flatness: very_dynamic
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: pure_tone
  spectral_complexity_mean: simple
  spectral_flux_normalized: chaotic
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: balanced

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 800.0000
  harmonic_decay_rate: -3.4356
  harmonic_regularity: 0.5527
  pitch_clarity: 101.5594
  inharmonicity: 0.0114
  type: complex
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -2.2588
  resonance_freq: 0.0000

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: Trig1 Example 1
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Classes/Trig1.html
// Tags: Trig1, Classes
// ---
// --- Example 1 ---
{ Trig1.ar(Dust.ar(1), 0.2) * FSinOsc.ar(800, 0.5) }.play


To create a fixed duration gate
(

SynthDef("trig1", { |dur = 0.125|
    var gate;
    gate = Trig1.kr(1.0, dur);
    OffsetOut.ar(0,
        SinOsc.ar(800, 0.3)
        * EnvGen.kr(
            Env([0, 0.1, 0.1, 0], [0.01, 1.0, 0.01], [-4, 4], 2),
            gate,
            doneAction: Done.freeSelf)
    )
}).add;

Routine({
    1.0.wait;
    100.do({
        s.sendBundle(0.05, ["s_new", "trig1", -1, 0, 0, 0, rrand(0.02, 0.25)]);
        0.25.wait
    })
}).play(SystemClock)

)

This should sound like a continuous sine wave, although it is actually a series of 0.25 second synths.
(
SynthDef("trig1", {
    var gate;
    gate = Trig1.kr(1.0, 0.25);
    OffsetOut.ar(0,
        SinOsc.ar(800, 0.3)
        * EnvGen.kr(
            Env([0, 0.1, 0.1, 0], [0.01, 1.0, 0.01], [-4, 4], 2),
            gate,
            doneAction: Done.freeSelf)
    )
}).add;

Routine({
    1.0.wait;
    100.do({
        s.sendBundle(0.05, ["s_new", "trig1", -1]);
        0.25.wait
    })
}).play(SystemClock)

)
